content:
When you edit a dataflow node, consider that changes can impact downstream nodes. If manually editing the JSON definition file, ensure changes are reflected in downstream nodes.

Renaming Node Names:
- When renaming a node in the JSON, check for uniqueness and update references in downstream nodes.
- In the dataflow editor, CRM Analytics validates unique names and updates downstream nodes automatically.

Adding Fields:
- Add fields to downstream nodes when adding a field in the dataflow JSON.
- Augment the new field on other data by adding it to the right_select parameter in augment nodes or the fields parameter in sliceDataset nodes with mode set to select.
- When adding fields in the dataflow editor, CRM Analytics offers to propagate changes.

Removing Fields:
- Remove fields from downstream nodes when removing a field in the dataflow JSON, including left_key, right_key, and right_select parameters in augment nodes and the fields parameter in sliceDataset nodes.
- Downstream computeExpression or computeRelative nodes referencing the field should be manually updated.
- In the dataflow editor, CRM Analytics offers to propagate changes when removing fields.
title: Editing Nodes in Dataflow for CRM Analytics
